HEADWORD: Jaborandi
<hw>Jab`o*ran"di</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The native name of a South American rutaceous shrub
(<spn>Pilocarpus pennatifolius</spn>). The leaves are used in medicine
as an diaphoretic and sialogogue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jaborine</ent>⟦br⟧
